You are analyzing code for **Timing Attack** vulnerabilities.

## What Is a Timing Attack?

A timing attack exploits measurable differences in the time an application takes to process different inputs. When comparing secrets (API keys, tokens, HMAC signatures, password reset tokens) using standard string comparison (`===`, `==`, `strcmp`), the comparison short-circuits at the first differing byte. An attacker can measure response times to infer the secret one character at a time. Constant-time comparison eliminates this side channel.

